title: Word Swap Comparison
comment: An experiment I have done before with similar parameters, changing a single word across multiple image generations, keeping the same seed and generation settings. This time the results were a bit different. While there are many similarities across the different images, the setting sun on the left contrasted by a blue sky to the right and the brownish buildings, the characters themselves were quite different. The last time I tried it, mostly only the face of the characters would change, not the overall pose and accessories. This might be due to the changes to how newer versions of Stable Diffusion generate images.

title: Prompt Engineering Comparison
comment: When looking at pictures generated by other Stable Diffusion users you often find very large prompts utilizing a lot tags describing the quality of the generated image. Words like ‘best quality’, ‘masterpiece’, ‘very detailed’, ‘8k’ and so on. What influence do these words have on the generated images? Well, this comparison tries to find that out by adding these words to a prompt and generating it with the same parameters’ multiple times. Is the result with the larges number of detail tags truly the best?

title: Generating a photo
comment: While Stable Diffusion XL 1.0 promises photorealistic generations my attempts to achieve these without additional LORA’s or Textual Inversions have been lacking. One of the major promises of SDXL was generation without using a lot of prompt engineering, yet the resulting image, while beautiful, seems more like a digital painting than a photo.

title: Generating a rat, cause rats are cool
comment: I have generated rats before with other Stable Diffusion models, and this must be one of the best ones yet. Older versions weren’t sure about the number of ears or appendages of a rat, often generating multiple sets of each. To see one that looks like a realistic rat fills me with joy.
